      "solution": "s=input().strip()\nm={'0':'0','1':'1','2':'5','5':'2','6':'9','8':'8','9':'6'}\nprint(\"INVALID\" if any(c not in m for c in s) else \"\".join(m[c] for c in s[::-1]))",
      "statement": "Given a number as a string of digits [[s]], replacing each digit with its mirror equivalent.\n\nThe mirror is obtained by:\n1. Reversing the digits .\n2. Replacing each digit with it's mirror equivalent.\n```\nMirror map:\n| Digit | Mirror |\n| ----- | ------ |\n| 0     | 0      |\n| 1     | 1      |\n| 2     | 5      |\n| 5     | 2      |\n| 6     | 9      |\n| 8     | 8      |\n| 9     | 6      |\n```\nAn invalid digit is any digit not present in the mirror map above <<(specifically: 3, 4, and 7)>>. If the input string contains any invalid digit, output {{INVALID}}.",
